# Schedule Grid Layout

## Structure
- Rows represent Units / Trucks
- Columns represent time in 15-minute increments
- Full day view (ex: 6:00 AM – 10:00 PM)

## Time Display
- Hour-by-hour breakdown
- Each hour divided into:
  - :00
  - :15
  - :30
  - :45

## Call Blocks
- Calls appear as rectangular blocks
- Block spans the duration of the appointment
  - 30 min = 2 time slots
  - 60 min = 4 time slots
  - 90 min = 6 time slots

## Current Time Indicator
- Vertical red line across schedule
- Moves in real-time

## Drag and Drop Rules
- Calls dragged from Pending Bar to unit row
- Drop allowed even if overlap occurs
- Hard warning popup appears if overlapping
- Dispatcher may override
- Overrides are logged

## Status Indicators
- Pending (Top Bar)
- Assigned (On Schedule)
- Completed (Faded or greyed out)